This plugin takes any HTML anchor elements that has `js:scroll` class in it and then will add a click event to it, which once clicked, it will scroll the current page into specific section that has an ID as defined in the fragment identifier. Default action is to scroll to the left and top of the page.

### Basic Usage

~~~ .html
<a class="js:scroll" href="#">Top</a>
~~~

~~~ .html
<a class="js:scroll" href="#form-comment">Add Comment</a>
~~~

### Advance Usage

Add these `data-*` attributes to customize the effect:

Option | Description
------ | -----------
`ease` | The [easing](http://robertpenner.com/easing "Robert Pennerâ€™s Easing Functions") type.
`hash-change` | Set to `true` to enable automatic URL hash addition once the scroll animation ends.

**Example:**

~~~ .html
<a class="js:scroll" href="#" data-ease="out-bounce">Top</a>
~~~

### Supported Easing Type

